I can give the example connected with the income of farmers.
We explained to our European partners that this is not about the fixed monthly income and therefore it cannot be taxed completely in advance.
We were answered that Tsipras's ministers never spoke about it.
That is, the Greek ministers were not prepared and badly informed, and therefore unsuccessfully conducted negotiations and concluded the unsuccessful agreement.
