We advanced reforms.
Of course, we lacked necessary determination and speed, but we acted in force majeure.
The market fell, and it was not visible the potential buyers ready to pay the price arranging the Greek government.
I at that time was a speaker of parliament, I managed to coordinate opinions of three parliamentary groups making then the government majority.
