The imported yachts will exempt from payment of the customs duties.
The Ministry of Economic Development intends to exempt temporarily imported yachts and other watercrafts for rest and sport from payment of the customs duties and taxes.
Corresponding changes in the list of preferential goods for temporary duty-free import were prepared by the ministry of an order of the Government of the Russian Federation.
About it Izvestia was reported by the Assistant Secretary of economic development Elena Lashkina.
In June, 2015 the prime minister of the Russian Federation Dmitry Medvedev following the results of a trip to the Crimea charged to a number of departments - to the Ministry of Economic Development, Ministry of Transport of the Russian Federation, Ministry of culture, the MFA, the Ministry of Emergency Situations, FSB, to FTS, Rostourism - to prepare offers on creating favorable conditions for yachting in coastal zones of the country.
In turn, experts note that the main problem is total absence of infrastructure for storage, service and the maintenance of yachts.
Owners prefer to store the vessels abroad - about €200 million annually go to treasury of the European states for maintenance, repair and service of yachts.
The Ministry of Economic Development of the Russian Federation prepared the draft decision of Council of the Euroasian economic commission "About modification of the Inventory, the customs duties which are temporarily imported with full conditional remission, taxes", providing full conditional remission of the customs duties, taxes concerning the imported yachts and other watercrafts for rest and sport.
According to the ministry, it, certainly, will promote creating favorable conditions for development of yachting in coastal zones of the country, - Lashkina noted.
The matter was submitted for consideration of a subcommittee on customs tariff, non-tariff regulation, protective measures in foreign trade of Government Commission on Economic Development and Integration which meeting took place in September, and following the results of discussion was also approved by departments.
As the representative of the Ministry of Economic Development noted, the proposed measure for full conditional release when importing is in essence a privilege.
Therefore after the approval of the minutes of a subcommittee in the government of the Russian Federation the Ministry of Economic Development will make the offer in the Euroasian economic commission for discussion with EEU member states, Lashkina explained.
The list of imported goods which are completely exempted from payment of the customs duties, taxes includes the goods necessary for rendering assistance of foreign economic activity and to the international cooperation, for application in the sphere of science, culture, cinematography, sport and tourism, for international assistance, etc. Among them - the office equipment (personal computers, typewriters), instrumentations, drilling equipment, scenic suits and scenery, mobile laboratories and workshops, a water ski, racing cars, motorcycles, sports aircraft, books, newspapers, magazines, musical instruments and objects for religious practices.
