The revenue of FedEx has the mixed character, decrease in forecasts for 2016.
FedEx reported on unfavourable results of the last quarter, and the giant of service of delivery reduced the forecast of annual profit because of decline in demand for services of a cargo transportation and growth of expenses in the division of land transportations.
Also the company declared that it plans to employ about 55 000 seasonal workers for holidays.
In the same time last year FedEx reported that it will employ 50 000 temporary employees for holidays.
Its actions fell in price approximately by 2,5 percent at the preliminary auction in 45 minutes prior to opening of the exchange on Wednesday.
FedEx Corp. declared that plans to earn from $10,40 to $10,90 in financial year which comes to an end next May that is 20 cents less, than in the previous forecast.
Analysts assumed $10,84 according to the review of FactSet.
Decrease in the forecast is observed despite raising of rates on average for 4,9 percent which will come into force on January 4, and growth of charges for land transportations heavy or cargoes within loading range which begins in November.
The company declared that it still plans growth of revenue in comparison with last year thanks to cut in expenditure, increase in gross revenue and growth of online trade.
The chairman and CEO Fred Smith declared that the company "worked steadily taking into account weak, in comparison with the forecast, economic conditions, especially in production and world trade".
Plans of hiring of labor on holidays were announced next day after the statement of the competitor, UPS, that they plan to hire in addition 95 000 employees, about the same as employed last year.
In a quarter which ended on August 31 FedEx earned 692 million dollars, is 6 percent more, than the previous year.
The income on an action made 2,42 dollars, is close to the forecast on average 2,44 dollars on an action which is carried out by Zacks Investment Research poll of 12 analysts.
The income increased by 5%, to 12,3 billion dollars.
Six analysts interviewed by Zacks assumed 12,23 billion dollars.
FedEx suffered from recession in the sector of urgent international transport in recent years that resulted in lack of growth of gross revenue in its division of express transportations.
However the boom of purchases on the Internet sharply improved results in FedEx Ground.
In the last quarter the proceeds from land transportations grew by 29%, however the operating income was left whole without changes because of the raised costs of large departures and self-insurance.
The division of express transportations gained higher income because of higher base rates whereas the income fell in the cargo sector because of increase in labor costs.
At the preliminary auction approximately for an hour before opening of the exchange of the stock FedEx fell to $3,85 or 2,5 percent - to $150,15.
They closed Tuesday, having dropped by 11 percent in a year and 17 percent below than a record of June 11.
On the most anticipated for several years to a meeting heads of the Federal Reserve System will spend two days this week at a 27-foot table from Honduran mahogany, deciding whether it is time to raise a key interest rate for the first time almost in ten years.
In one end of richly decorated room for meetings height to two floors over them the wall image of the United States will hang.
This card - a reminder that the chairman of the Federal Reserve System Janet L. Yellen and her colleagues have to put economic interests of the country above all others.
The central bank received a double assignment from the Congress: as much as possible to increase employment in the USA and to keep here the stable prices.
But since Great recession heads of Federal system recognized that there is also the third, unwritten assignment: financial stability.
And this third assignment can be an unknown factor in almost predicted decision which will be declared on Thursday, whether the economy of the USA is ready to coming off the unprecedented incentive provided with almost zero short-term interest rate since the end of 2008.
Even while the majority of data show steady growth of economy, recent shocks in the world financial markets can keep careful heads of Federal system from addition of volatility by a raising of a base rate for federal funds as it is - even only on a quarter of percentage point.
"It is obvious that labor market and inflation will become the first and most important subject of consideration", - told Lindsay M. Piegza, the chief economist of Stifel Nicolaus & Co broker company.
"However I think that if they looked for the reason not to raise the stakes, the increased uncertainty around the world market is enough to give them a justification to wait further", - she noticed.
There is no consensus about what will be made in the Federal Reserve System that in itself provokes fluctuations of the financial market.
About a half of the economists who are recently interviewed by Bloomberg predicted growth of an interest rate this week.
The financial markets, however, expect that the Federal system from it will keep, thus that the key indicator shows only approximately 30 percent probability of fast rise.
It can lead to stock market falling if the Federal system raises a rate provided that those who make decisions will not soften blow the promise that the following increase will be at a distant day.
On Tuesday the Dow Jones index rose by 228,89 points, or for 1,4%, to 16 599,85.
Take-off was provoked by expectations of the fact that the persons defining the strategy of Federal system will leave a rate this week, - John Lonski, the chief economist of the Moody's Capital Markets Research group declared.
"Will be a surprise if the Federal system raises rates in this timepoint", - he noticed.
If the management of the Federal Reserve System acts this way, "they should come far in the adoption of the strategy to hold the financial markets in hand that they did not panic".
Other experts objected that increase in a rate could calm the financial markets as it will remove uncertainty on the subject of how the Federal system will work.
In total a month ago the Federal system, apparently, inclined to raise a rate for 0,25% this month, doing the first small short step in slow toughening of financial conditions that could confirm durability of restoration of the USA.
Yellen declared in the spring and at the beginning of summer that she expects increase in a rate this year, despite complaints from liberals that bigger economic progress is necessary.
Though emergence of new jobs in August was slowed down, growth of labor market was stable this year.
Unemployment was reduced to 5,1% last month that is the lowest indicator for more than seven years, and almost at that level which in Federal system is considered full employment.
Growth of the salary shows acceleration signs.
And, though inflation continues to be below the annual indicator planned by the central bank in 2%, the management of Federal system declared that the temporary effect of sharp drop in oil prices became the key reason.
The economy "can cope also with higher rates, and needs them, taking into account labor market reduction," - Ian Sheferdson, the chief economist of Pantheon Macroeconomics noticed.
However worldwide began to shake the financial markets at the end of the last month after China devaluated the currency.
