In Domodedovo there took place a business "game in the airport".
In the capital test new form of education.
Four hundred students tried out as the staff of the airport.
For this purpose in Domodedovo mounted models of three airports.
Young people not only examined and registered passengers, but also served planes.
All this is in the form of a business game, however on complexity it did not concede reality.
The late flights, at once two passengers with changes onboard, the ladder was lost somewhere on the way to the plane.
For the real airport - hell.
For this purpose, which was proved in a hangar of Domodedovo - a standard set of tasks which beginners should solve.
In one hangar three airport terminals from the different countries of the world went in at once.
In them four hundred students from capital colleges and higher education institutions work today.
Unprecedented chance to learn everything about inner world of airport.
Registration of passengers, service of planes, baggage turn - to them entrusted even buses on the airfield, ladders and examination of passengers.
And passengers - entirely problem.
At one disorder with documents, another was late for flight, the third filled a bag with suspicious objects.
And it is necessary to deal with all this, as in life - in the minimum time.
For each of these carried-out tasks it charges a certain sum, virtual money as though the airline paid them the corresponding sums for flight service.
"For non-performance of the corresponding tasks the penalty is collected from them", - the financial analyst of a game Dmitry Hilko explains in an interview to the Vesti-Moscow program.
The events are fixedly watched by officials from the Ministry of Education.
For them this examination - attempt to test new form of education.
Already found it the place it is aware of secondary professional education.
"Six interregional centers of competence which will become, in fact, new models of activity of modern colleges with a modern control system, with highly skilled personnel, with the modern equipment will be created", - the director of the department of state policy in the sphere of training of personnel and additional professional education of the Ministry of Education and Science of the Russian Federation Natalya Zolotareva tells.
But to students - not to global plans.
After three days of such training they, it seems, need day off.
But estimates for this examination had quite material expression.
The latest smart points, the best which I ever saw!
"I received them for the fact that I in due time answered a claim to our airport in Instagram", - the participant of a game, the PR manager of the team Frankfurt Airport Sergei Shuvalov is happy.
Judges that is called wrote down the best that by the time of completion of study to invite to themselves to work.
The U.S. Embassy regrets for closure of the American center in Moscow.
The American Embassy in Russia expressed a regret in connection with closure of the American center operating at Library of foreign literature.
The center worked in Moscow more than 22 years.
The U.S. Embassy in Moscow deeply regrets for the unilateral decision of the Russian government to close the American center of the U.S. Embassy at the All-Russian state library of M.I. Rudomino in Moscow.
"The unilateral steps taken by the Russian Federation recently call into question commitment of the government of Russia to communications between the Russian and American people which were not interrupted even at the time of Cold War and at other difficult moments of a long story of the relations of our countries", - it is said in the statement of the ambassador of the USA John Tefft which came to Interfax.
The American Center created deep and strong communications between people and culture of Russia and the United States.
It represented the center of the American culture, history and literature in the Russian capital, and also served as the venue of meetings with numerous American eminent persons among whom there were astronauts, actors, athletes, scientists, politicians and writers.
"Only last year the American center held more than 400 cultural and educational events and accepted more than 50 thousand Russian visitors", - the diplomat emphasized.
Tefft reminded that about a year ago the decision to close one more joint Russian-American project - the program of educational exchanges of FLEX (Future Leaders Exchange Program) was made.
The green Tribunal was fast on punishment.
Typical situation: four officials face a table of the judge Swatanter Kumar, listening to his claims to the done work.
The court is not satisfied with quality of your work at all.
We not for this purpose provided you the 110-page order that you laughed at it, - Kumar says. -
If at least one more brick is put, we will order to demolish all available constructions.
Kumar heads the National Green Tribunal (NGT) - the body of judicial authority founded in 2010 to stop the rapid environmental pollution accompanying the rapid economic growth of the last decades.
During this time the Tribunal managed to consider more than 10 thousand claims connected with air pollution, collecting garbage, geological developments, toxic waste and construction of dams.
In two of three cases the court makes the decision on the termination of the construction leading to pollution.
Rates are incredibly high: for incomplete 60 years, passed from the moment of declaration of independence of the strengthened industrial development India turned from the country of the virgin jungle into one of the most overpopulated and polluted countries of the world.
Especially the problem is particularly acute in large megalopolises where development of infrastructure does not keep up with a prompt urbanization: the cities are covered with a dense smog, the rivers are filled with pesticides and waste of the enterprises and households, and the few remained inhabited massifs are cut down under building by new residential quarters.
Despite formal support of the green movement from the state, the NGT is regularly exposed to criticism from Narendra Modi's government as often becomes the main reason of cancellation of the largest investment projects.
So, in May of this year the minister of the environment called the judgments "extreme" and "impracticable".
Sometimes the judgments cannot really be executed in the time put by court, the lawyer on ecological affairs Raj Panjwani confirms.
However impracticable deadlines have also a positive side: at least, they force responsible persons to move.
"Its main goal - to shake up this system", - the lawyer adds.
The green Tribunal already repeatedly cancelled major projects: on its account the termination of construction of the airport, power plant and hundreds of smaller constructions.
At the same time try not to forget about people too: for example, during discussion of destiny of the pharmaceutical company in Telagnan's staff polluting the local river fluoride.
We can close your factory, but we are responsible also for economic consequences.
"People will lose work", - Kumar commented on the decision.
However similar explanations not always find understanding at simple people whose life can change thanks to one stroke of a judicial feather.
So, in April the Tribunal made the decision to forbid all vehicles 10 years entry into the capital are more senior, than caused public indignation.
Despite sharply fallen popularity and a barrage of criticism, Swatanter Kumar refused to cancel this decision.
Instead he ordered from the government of Delhi statistics about the driving and leaving motor transport, and also made the offer to buy 10 thousand additional buses, previously having learned at factories whether they are able to execute the similar order.
As such sources of pollution as dumps, quality of fuel began to get to the sphere of attention of court and even road incidents, people's wrath began to calm down gradually.
But the program for cleaning of the Ganges River with a pomp announced by the prime minister Narendra Modi last year became the most sore subject of the basic judge.
When it comes about Ganges - the river, sacred for Hindus, the judge often ceases to constrain the emotions and passes to shout.
You know what means the word "sacred"?
Someone poured out water of Ganges on God's statue, and in it there were excrements, - the judge gets excited. -
You continue to pollute the river because you think: Ganges is Ganges, it will take away all our sins.
It is the river which we worship, and look what you do with it every day.
Cleaning of Ganges is the most ambitious and expensive ecological project announced by the new government.
Now the quantity of fecal bacteria in this river exceeds norm more than by 120 times.
Annually from 1,5 to 3 of 700 million Hindus bathing in it die of infectious diseases.
In February Narendra Modi even offered in Fund of rescue of Ganges the money gained from sale of his suit in which it met Barack Obama and 455 more objects from his personal collection.
Ecologists right there accused the prime minister of populism: the suit was bought for 700 thousand dollars while on cleaning of the river not less than eight billion are required.
Supporters of Green Tribunal agree that India should go still a long way before it is able to call itself the developed country, however at the same time do not consider that at the price of progress there has to be an ecology.
"In developing country a talk on the environment is often perceived as unattainable luxury, - the activist of the Call of Ganges organization Malika Bhanot says. -
And the court tries to find golden mean between ecology and development".
