Where I can leave a comment about work of the bailiff in Murmansk?
The Office of the Federal Bailiff Service for Murmansk region reported that for improvement of work on protection of the rights and legal interests of citizens and the organizations in department there is a book for feedback and suggestions.
In it citizens can leave record about quality of work of court bailiffs and other officials of management, information about substandard work, and also to express the suggestions and wishes.
In management the copy of the book for feedback and suggestions is in the central hall, in a special pocket on the visible and available place by the building's checkpoint.
In structural divisions of management the book is in office.
Taking into account the nature of the feedback or suggestion in necessary cases to his initiator a written response is sent.
Xi Jinping urges to make economy more open for the world
The economy has to become more open for the whole world to fuel its growth as the president Xi Jinping in the address to group which the task of the leadership in reforms faces told on Tuesday.
"China has to concentrate on attracting foreign investment and expertize and improve opening-up policies", - he told, addressing participants of the 16th meeting of the Central Leading Group for Deepening Overall Reform.
According to him, promoting opening up and pushing forward reforms will give to economy a new impulse and vital force and will provide new room for economic growth.
The leading group adopted a series of guidelines, including on introduction of regulation of access for investors to the market, change of the rules of border control, encouraging state-owned enterprises (SOE) attracting the private capital and overhauling the resident registration system.
According to the statement, the list of sectors of economy and the production inaccessible for investment will be made.
The system will be gradually debugged by means of trial programs.
It is an important step as it will give the market a bigger role in distribution of resources, to ensuring a law-based business environment and increase in openness, as they say in the statement.
The government will also loosen controls over the powers conferred to them to the companies, guaranteeing thereby that the companies will do the business.
In the statement it is also said that China will allow border areas to explore new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms for promoting regional growth.
Even more spheres will be available to private investors for the purpose of opening up state-controlled sectors.
"The government will not change the policy toward foreign investment and will protect legal interests of foreign-funded companies, and also to provide them the best conditions", - is said in the statement.
The procedure of applying for permanent residence permits, or "Green Card", will be in addition facilitated by way of optimizing requirements and simplification of the process of giving.
Ensuring the rights of lawyers and questions of training of professional judges and public prosecutor's workers were also discussed at a meeting.
According to a statement released after the meeting, at it there were also a prime minister Li Keqiang and ministers Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli.
